#Data Cleaning

#change the data type
dailyActivity$ActivityDate<-mdy(dailyActivity$ActivityDate)

#Merge data

#Hourly Data
hourlyActivity<-merge(hourlyCalories,hourlyIntensities,by=c("Id","ActivityHour"))
hourlyActivity<-merge(hourlyActivity,hourlySteps,by=c("Id","ActivityHour"))

#Calculation and Analysis ##Usage frequency

#Count the frequency
#hourly activity
hourlyFreq<-data.frame(table(hourlyActivity$Id))
colnames(hourlyFreq)<-c("Id","HourlyFreq")
#weight
weightFreq<-data.frame(table(weight$Id))
colnames(weightFreq)<-c("Id","WeightFreq")
#sleep day
sleepDayFreq<-data.frame(table(sleepDay$Id))
colnames(sleepDayFreq)<-c("Id","SleepDayFreq")
#heartrate
heartrateFreq<-data.frame(table(heartrate$Id))
colnames(heartrateFreq)<-c("Id","HeartrateFreq")

#Merge data
mergeFreq<-merge(hourlyFreq,weightFreq,by="Id",all=T)
mergeFreq<-merge(mergeFreq,sleepDayFreq,by="Id",all=T)
mergeFreq<-merge(mergeFreq,heartrateFreq,by="Id",all=T)

summary(mergeFreq)

##user weight, sleep quality

#mean BMI
meanBMI<-weight%>%group_by(Id)%>%summarise_at(vars(BMI), list(meanBMI = mean))%>%as.data.frame()

#Relationship between sleep quality and activity
sleepDay$sleepOnsetLatency<-as.numeric(sleepDay$TotalTimeInBed-sleepDay$TotalMinutesAsleep)
meanSleepOnsetLatency<-sleepDay%>%group_by(Id)%>%summarise_at(vars(sleepOnsetLatency),list(meanSleepOnsetLatency=mean))%>%as.data.frame()
sleepQuality<-merge(sleepDay[,c("Id","TotalMinutesAsleep")],meanSleepOnsetLatency,by="Id")

#Analysis ##Descriptive Statistic

##Draw the trend line for frequency

weightPlot<-ggplot(mergeFreq)+geom_point(mapping=aes(x=HourlyFreq,y=WeightFreq))+labs(title='Frequency: hourly activity VS weight')

##Find the relationship between different variables

allData<-merge(allData,mergeFreq,by="Id")
